    <title>Installing and configuring &kdump;</title>
    <abstract><para>This topic covers how to install and configure &kdump;.</para></abstract>
    </info>
<para>To install &kdump;;</para>
 <screen>&prompt.sudo; <command>zypper install kdump </command> </screen>
 <para>This command downloads the following packages:</para>
 <itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><command>kdump</command></para></listitem>
<listitem><para><command>kexec-tools</command></para></listitem>
<listitem><para><command>makedumpfile</command></para></listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
 <para>&kdump; recommends:</para>
 <itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>To store the vmcore file remotely:</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Install the <package>cifs-utils</package> package to store on Samba stores. </para></listitem>
<listitem><para>Install the <package>lftp</package> package to store on FTP / SFTP servers. </para></listitem>
<listitem><para> Install the <package>nfs-client</package> package to store on NFS servers.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para> Install the <package>openssh-clients</package> package to store over SSH.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</listitem>
<listitem><para>The <literal>mailx</literal> utility to enable sending notifications when a crash dump is saved. </para></listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
